{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsMrYcNQeumPQ8sBzyAC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both requirements verified.\n\n**Root cause:** Neither `rate-api` nor `rate-health` ingress had any rate-limiting annotations, so `/api` was unthrottled. (A decoy ingress `rate-api-alt-hard` for a different host was left untouched.)\n\n**Fix:** Annotated only the `rate-api` ingress:\n```\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"2\"\nnginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"\n```\nThis generates `limit_req zone=... rate=2r/s burst=2 nodelay;` applied solely to the `/api` location — confirmed via the live nginx.conf, and confirmed `/health` has no `limit_req` directive at all.\n\n**Verified:** Burst traffic to `/api` returns `200 200 200 503 503 ...` (rate-limited after burst is exhausted), while burst traffic to `/health` returns all `200`s. No application Deployments were modified."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":405,"cache_read_input_tokens":64612,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":405},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8c38299f-a84f-4c3b-a911-5f9c970cd4c0","uuid":"31088c37-705a-451c-aa7e-a0ce9f48d22a","request_id":"req_011CcsMrXWtYMg7tFa92Vixg"}
